title: Radiochemical determination of the absolute yields of fragments of the fission of Pu241 and Pu239 by slow neutrons

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Atomic Energy, Vol.31, p.804 (1971)

x4freetext: Radiochemical determination of the absolute yields of
fragments of the fission of Pu241 and Pu239 by slow
Neutron flux with Cd ratio 4.26 ( for gold).

x4code.hlp: Data converted from file of B.F.Rider

x4freetext: Relative data were added in Subents 004,006.

x4headers.headerHelp: Dummy incident proj. energy, for broad spectrum

x4freetext: Mica detectors to measure number of fissions.
Mica detectors with applied Pu were packed together
with the working targets into Al foil beakers.
Mean square error of number of fissions,
including dilution and application of the solutions,
count of number of tracks, efficiency of mica.
Error of chemical yields for Ce - 2-3%.

x4freetext: Mean square error of four to ten experiments
